description: Organisers say the extra date is being added due to "high demand".
title: Second Biffy Cylro date added to Eden Sessions
title_page: Second Biffy Cylro date added to Eden Sessions  - BBC News
maintext:
Scottish rockers Biffy Clyro will play a second date at the Eden Project due to "very high demand", organisers have announced.
The band was originally slated to play the Eden Sessions on 9 July but will now perform the following evening as well.
Though they have performed headline sets at Reading and Leeds Festivals, Download Festival, TRNSMT and Isle of Wight Festival, this is the first time they will play the Cornwall event.
Tickets will go on general sale at 15:30 GMT on Monday.
